==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Floret
<hw>Flo"ret</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>florete</ets>, F. <ets>fleurette</ets>, dim. of OF. <ets>lor</ets>,
F. <ets>fleur</ets>. See <er>Flower</er>, and cf. <er>Floweret</er>, 3d
<er>Ferret</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A little
flower; one of the numerous little flowers which compose the head or
anthodium in such flowers as the daisy, thistle, and dandelion.</def>
<rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[F. <ets>fleuret</ets>.]</ety> <def>A foil; a blunt
sword used in fencing.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Cotgrave.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Floriage</ent>⟦br⟧
